Head to Head Analysis: Colfax Corporation (CFX) versus Graco (GGG)


					Posted by Oliver Carreras on Jul 23rd, 2017 // No Comments




Colfax Corporation (NYSE: CFX) and Graco (NYSE:GGG) are both mid-cap industrial products companies, but which is the superior investment? We will contrast the two companies based on the strength of their profitabiliy, dividends, institutional ownership, earnings, analyst recommendations, risk and valuation. 
Dividends


 Get Colfax Corporation alerts:



Graco pays an annual dividend of $1.44 per share and has a dividend yield of 1.3%. Colfax Corporation does not pay a dividend. Graco pays out 135.9% of its earnings in the form of a dividend, suggesting it may not have sufficient earnings to cover its dividend payment in the future. Graco has raised its dividend for 12 consecutive years. 





Analyst Ratings
This is a breakdown of current ratings and recommmendations for Colfax Corporation and Graco, as reported by MarketBeat. 



