Frequently Asked Questions for Colfax Corporation (NYSE:CFX)
What is Colfax Corporation's stock symbol?

Colfax Corporation trades on the New York Stock Exchange (NYSE) under the ticker symbol "CFX."



How were Colfax Corporation's earnings last quarter?

Colfax Corporation (NYSE:CFX) posted its earnings results on Friday, July, 28th. The company reported $0.43 earnings per share for the quarter, hitting the Thomson Reuters' consensus estimate of $0.43. The company had revenue of $965.83 million for the quarter, compared to analyst estimates of $940.31 million. Colfax Corporation had a net margin of 3.98% and a return on equity of 6.29%. The business's revenue for the quarter was up .9% compared to the same quarter last year. During the same period last year, the business posted $0.41 earnings per share.  View Colfax Corporation's Earnings History.



When will Colfax Corporation make its next earnings announcement?

Colfax Corporation is scheduled to release their next quarterly earnings announcement on Friday, July, 28th 2017. View Earnings Estimates for Colfax Corporation.



What guidance has Colfax Corporation issued on next quarter's earnings?

Colfax Corporation updated its FY17 earnings guidance on Friday, July, 28th. The company provided earnings per share guidance of $1.65-1.75 for the period, compared to the Thomson Reuters consensus earnings per share estimate of $1.73. 



Where is Colfax Corporation's stock going? Where will Colfax Corporation's stock price be in 2017?

12 equities research analysts have issued twelve-month price targets for Colfax Corporation's stock. Their predictions range from $26.00 to $50.00. On average, they expect Colfax Corporation's share price to reach $42.86 in the next twelve months. View Analyst Ratings for Colfax Corporation.



Who are some of Colfax Corporation's key competitors?

 Some companies that are related to Colfax Corporation include W.W. Grainger (GWW), Smith (A.O.) Corporation (AOS), AB SKF (SKFRY), IDEX Corporation (IEX), Sealed Air Corporation (SEE), Avery Dennison Corporation (AVY), Crown Holdings (CCK), The Middleby Corporation (MIDD), Allegion PLC (ALLE), BPC Acquisition Corp (BERY), Nordson Corporation (NDSN), Alcoa Corp. (AA), HD Supply Holdings (HDS), Hubbell (HUBB), Donaldson Company (DCI), Flowserve Corporation (FLS), Graco (GGG) and AGCO Corporation (AGCO).



